- There is NO way Sony can stop showEQ to work.<br>
- There is NO technical way sony can be sure to detect showEQ.  <br>
Scan Network layer?  Ok i scan direcly your memory or i change my network dlls by an hacked one that will hide SEQ or thouthand of other hacks that i don't know about.<br>
Basically, you, home windows user, have total access on your computer, can install all that you want on it, can read everything from everywhere on your computer. This little key has nowhere to hide. The showEQ program could change its signature. You cannot be sure to find it.<br>
<br>
As for legual issues. <br>
- Very poor image of the company. I am sure Sony don't want to become officially the company that spies your hard disk. <br>
- Laws are not the same everywhere. I am pretty sure that in France this part of this Eula would be declared null. Basically when a part of a contract is abusive, it is ignored.<br>
- People are really touchy about their privacy on their computer. No one (even the judge) will permit the slightest move toward Big brother. No SOE will not be watching you. <br>
- There are in every country organisations that exist just for the sake of protecting people's rights relative to computers. As they are backed by the states they have money, they are backed by good lawyers too. In certain contries they make laws and have their own judgment process. Some of them are just immune to big companies.<br>
<br>
I don't think SOE weighted well their decision. Maybe when they took it they bet that the SEQ programers would never port it to windows as it was the initial policy of the SEQ project. Now they have all the power of the nerds of open source to deal with. I am still trying hard to find a single security system that the user have full access to that has not been violated. <br>
<br>
I think SEQ is bad, before it was not so bad because just a few have access to dual combo box with linux and windows and a cable connection (You need to use ethernet to be able to sniff a network, good luck sniffing an USB connection or a normal modem). Now everyone has access to it, even if just 10% of the player base will use it (optimistic from my point of view) then the game is completely wasted. <br>
<br>
