<br>
If EQ tries to scan the Hard-Drive, SEQ could modify the patcher (or actual EQ) to scan for a slightly modified filename.  The same principle can be applied to any other scanning method that EQ might employ.<br>
<br>
Alternatively, instead of modifying EQ or the patcher SEQ could do a number of things to become quite stealthy.<br>
<br>
Dont get me wrong, I'm no fan of SEQ.  I appreciate the benefits from some of the information posted by SEQ users, and wish VI had made that same information directly available.  But SEQ is too easily abused, and hurts others by making them disadvantaged because they want to play the game the way it was meant to play.<br>
<br>
But the end result is, regardless of your feelings on SEQ - it becomes a war of wills.  Because every change VI puts in to stop SEQ can be countered by SEQ designers.  It's just an issue of whose willing to keep going the longest.<br>
<br>
