<br>
Well that is theory, at least =). Hard to uphold on the internet, but the purpose is to show that the legal implications of having disclaimers vary a lot. In Denmark, they are usually not worth the bytes they are written on, if they itend to take away consumer rights. You don't have to be a lawyer in DK to buy stuff, you just have to have common sense. <br>
<br>
in B2B it is different however. But clearly not the case here.<br>
<br>
btw, I am not a lawyer, but a friend explained this to me once. I apologize for any errors that I may have added. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=magnomightymidget>MagnoMightymidget</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 88<br> <font color=#333333>(11/4/02 6:54:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7687.topic&index=95>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   RE: International legal spaghetti</span><hr size=1> Personally I don't care if VI bans every user of showEQ, it would mean less crowded spots for me. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  The thing that DOES concern me about all this sh@t is that the ONLY way Verrant could find those people using showEQ is for them to search your computer and or memory to see if showEQ is running.  That is a complete violation of the information privacy act and they could be looking at huge fines and prison sentences if they did that without your express permission.  Sooo that means they'd have to modify the EULA to allow them access to information on your machine freely and I'm sorry but I'll never press the 'agree' button again if they do that.  I don't run 3rd party programs in the background but I do value my privacy and verrant has no business knowing what's on my computer. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START >: --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/mad.gif ALT=">:"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=yanbun>Yanbun</A></span><b